39-48, Butcher Block Mountains<br>
Minimum Level: 39<br>
Maximum Level: 48<br>
Zone Name: Butcher Block Mountains<br>
Camp Name: Den &amp; Friends<br>
Mob List: Den IronBlade, +2 other dwarven females and a male dwarf fishing along the coast.<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 4 <br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 9 <br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 2 (very easy)<br>
Faction Affected: Citizens of Kaladim decreased from Den and the two dwarven females, Guards decreased if you kill the fishing dwarf as well.<br>
<br>
Other Notes/Tips/Warnings: This is an awesome camp, great money, and awesome XP. Now granted, when I did this camp from 44-48, there was no KEI in the game, so perhaps now its faster elsewhere, but without KEI, you can med up to full just in time for these guys to repop. I imagine with KEI you could quad these dwarves, then go quad the dwarves up by the docs as well, and still get back before a re-pop. The money here is excellent and really, do you even want dwarf faction? Heck no.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Often camped, but not so much anymore as people don't want to ruin faction.<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Amazing plat making possibilities. Each dwarf drops 1-2pp in coins, and items worth between 3-15pp, and there is a druid vendor right near where you kite them. Can easily make several hundred plat an hour here.<br>
