 <br>
43-45, Permafrost Keep<br>
Minimum Level: 43<br>
Maximum Level: 45<br>
Zone Name: Permafrost Keep<br>
Camp Area/LOC: Bear/Spider/Wolf Pit under Vox lair<br>
Mob List (HP): Giant Polar Bear, Giant Dire Wold, Wooly Spider<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 8 (depends on server)<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 3<br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 7<br>
Faction Affected: None<br>
<br>
Other Notes/Tips/Warnings: Alrighty, not sure if anyone is still keeping this a secret or whatever since PoP came out ...but I'm done with it and going to spill the beans. First off to any naysayers, this is perfectly doable, did it for probably 40 or so AA points. I'm going to assume whoever tries this knows a thing or two about quadding and such. It took a little time to find the non-warping path to quad down there but since that is probably all you need to know if you're reading this here it is. Go to the main area where the ladder is, start off by pulling and killing the Ice Witch solo, stay away from directly near the ladder as there are two (2) quad mobs there that will assist if you get too close, but as long as your level is sufficient single pulling is easy. Finish Ice Witch<br>
Now go to the safe corner, the little indented corner where the big rock is in the ground ..the one opposite the side of this big area that the ladder is on. That it the safe spot down there. Snare pull the 2 mobs near the ladder, then the 2 in front of the dire wolf cubby hole. Round them up by making circles around the 2 large rocks, go from the safe corner, to the corner a bit to left of the rock opposite, you'll see it's as far as you can get on that wall. Snare them then start the quad. You have just a little more time than you need to go to one corner, Pillar, run around one rock to next corner, Pillar, and so on. Circle should be clockwise, big rock on your right each time you run around it.<br>
<br>
Successive pulls can be determined by any experienced quadder as to what is to your liking. I always then pulled the the dire wolf cubby if four (4) in there, if not ..pulled they and polar bears at ramp down. Once you are pulling the bears on lower level, go to middle of the wall with no bears on it to snare the ones at bottom of ramp, and then grab another two (2) down there, or vice versa.<br>
<br>
Epic is a huge help down here but not necessary, and manastone is lovely, but this is still a viable option for those lacking either that are after great XP level 60 and below for a little risk. Do not to try to quad elsewhere down there though aside from around those two (2) big rocks, corner to corner, or they will warp onto you and make things go all ugly.<br>
Hope this helps some people and is as productive for you as it was for me.<br>
<br>
Submitted by: Remlap<br>
<br>
 <br>
44-50, Lake of Ill Omen (Bloodgills)<br>
Minimum Level: 44<br>
Maximum Level: 50<br>
Zone Name: Lake of Ill Omen<br>
Camp Area/LOC: Underwater Ruins<br>
Mob List (HP): Bloodgill Goblin (1400), Bloodgill Marauder (3000)<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 8 <br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 5 <br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 7 <br>
Faction Affected: Pirates of Gunthak increased, Bloodgills decreased<br>
<br>
Other Notes/Tips/Warnings: 200 swimming and steelskin recommended to minimize damage on close pulls. Enduring Breath not required but handy while scouting invis. Levitate up at all times, staff of tflux a must! There are two (2) Bloodgill Goblins at each pillar (four (4) total), you can pull one pair, swim up and make some distance levitating on the water with JBoots/SoW before pulling the second pair. Once complete head towards the beach for roundup, snare and AE's (if SoWed, zigzag or you may lose them). Middle underwater building can also be pulled but are down deeper - hard to make a quad of this without taking a beating though, unless Marauder is up: in the doorway and hard to spot underwater, not having the blue skin that the Bloodgill Goblins have nowadays. Social, low aggro range underwater (might force you to tflux both goblins for each pair). <br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Pretty remote, not much competition.<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Some pp, research stuff, sometimes a Harpoon of the Depths.<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The pulling requires some practice since you have to dive underwater to pull.<br>
<br>
