51-54, Cobalt Scar<br>
Minimum Level: 51<br>
Maximum Level: 54<br>
Zone Name: Cobalt Scar<br>
Camp Area/LOC: Next to the TP ring<br>
Mob List (HP): Wyverns<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 2<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 7 (they drop gems)<br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 3 (just avoid the named)<br>
Faction Affected: COV on named Yvolcarm<br>
<br>
Other Notes/Tips/Warnings: Often camped but very easy, Wyverns will not agro if you have a good faction with Claws of Veeshan, except for Yvolcarm and Azureake (the named Cobalt Drake). So stay away from them when they are up, they are not snarable neither rootable. Killing them will decrease your CoV faction. If you aggro, just run and then gate. Need to be Dubious to CoV to travel safely here. <br>
<br>
Submitted by: Orzabald<br>
<br>
NOTE: With KEI, I already did Wyverns at level 49 using BoF and CoF. Sure it takes longer and you have to re-snare once or twice, but it's very doable. <br>
<br>
Submitted by: Traxam<br>
<br>
NOTE: Wyverns begin to go light blue at level 52 and the XP plummets. They are quite doable when Eastern Wastes begins to go green. Wyverns are not casters. Drakes are. Drakes also dispell. You can take them by singling, rooting, and nuking from max range. Also beware Yvolcarn. He looks like a wyvern, spawns like a wyvern, but is immune to run speed changes like root/shackle. Know where he is before you pull.<br>
<br>
Also, you can pull from the tower if you either run up it, or target through the window and t-flux while near. Be careful of the bulgar (or whatever they are called, leader is immune to run speed changes and will aggro nearest.)<br>
