<br>
The tower spectres have the tenacious custom to airdrop on top of you, if they get stuck in the tower. They will do this usually when you're about to clear the water.<br>
<br>
Learn to octa-kite. You will almost always get at least 1 of the spectres from the tower itself as well, and I have managed all 8 when one of the corner spectres climbed the tower.<br>
<br>
I always have O'Keils Levity up, and am using a horse and C3 or better. Tflux one of the corner specs, and run in circles around the edges of the island, tfluxing the tower specs if they won't add. This will group them nicely, ready for 2 nicely packaged BoF casts, when you pull them to the flat areas near SRo. Both groups can stay within cast range, so BoF the 2nd group occasionally, and switch your attention on them when making a half-circle, or they'll lose interest and suddenly vanish....<br>
<br>
After this, the spectres should spawn in quads again, unless you killed all 8 within a short timeframe. This can give you 50-100pp, and about 10pct exp on lvl 43.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=braellaendressari>Braellaen Dressari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/3/03 2:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bump</span><hr size=1> Bump, why not sticky it too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ziggyholiday>ziggyholiday</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/3/03 6:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bump</span><hr size=1> IMO I would stop quadding spirocs at 51, and even at 51 exp is crap...head to CS or just group for a bit /shrug<br>
