Minimum Level: 60+, with raid gear. generally 65 + aa<br>
Maximum Level: 65<br>
Camp Area/LOC: Entrance or a basement, preferably the recuso trial area(Alekson Garn)<br>
Mob List (HP): Valorians at 26k hp about. The black suits(but not black valiant spirits) at ent as well, quad them towards the back of the clear area. it is faster than valorians, but the xp for what it takes to kill a mob I believe is less.<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 8 on Kane Bayle; 90% of the time I am alone in zone. the 10 mobs wont suffice where you'd want 12 in a basement, more are available at the ent but lesser xp and require an odd way to break the camp.<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 7. specs, other random loot very rarely. goodies to make sandwiches, probably the main draw for me to loot the mobs, are very common.<br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 1<br>
Faction Affected: Battalion of Marr. What this faction is for remains a mystery to me.<br>
<br>
Notes...<br>
<br>
Basement- quadding this one is easy, dont fall asleep while you do it! grab the mobs and quad them to the side of the room, away from the picture-thingy on the floor. turning around will slow down the quad(slowing xp) so I recommend that you try to zig zag back and forth. mobs walking along the hypotenuse of an isoscolese right triangle as opposed to just going straight when you zig zag must spend 40% more time just to get to the same place! that's 40% more damage you can do before you must engage yourself in another time consuming turn.<br>
<br>
Clear area with a tree(ent)- you can pull mobs from here and quad it in the area that has the solitary tree in it, which ill call the courtyard. when you have the mobs, quad them in a pentagonal pattern in order to kill them without having to turn. chain nuke pol/pof power! pulling them is a bit more difficult than the valorians, so I'd give the difficulty of this camp a '2', rather 1.2 (no adds or anything!). you can get mobs from deeper in easily, but it can depend on your load time. if its fast, run the 2 mobs at ent to the back of the courtyard and snare them. when theyre at the back of the wall you can abscond, get 2 more and reaggro the stationary guards.<br>
<br>
hope this one helped :P. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mtw333>mtw333</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/03 1:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Flies in PoD</span><hr size=1> Just a quick tag:<br>
